'''{{Colour|red|Warning}}:''' [[Venenatis]] resides in a [[multi-way]] area in moderately high-level [[Wilderness]]. You may be attacked at any time during the fight, and this is always a possibility in any deep wilderness [[multicombat area]]. '''Do not''' bring any items that you are not willing to lose. Items like the [[Dragon defender]] are '''permanently''' lost if not protected beyond level 20 Wilderness. 

[[Venenatis]] is a level 464 [[spider]] [[boss]] that is found in the [[Silk Chasm]]. [[Spindel]] is the level 302 lesser variant of Venenatis found in the [[Web Chasm]], but otherwise her mechanics are identical. Completion of the medium [[Wilderness Diary]] is required to fight Venenatis.

==Transportation==
Venenatis is located in the [[Silk Chasm]], which is a lair in the far east of the Wilderness at level 35.

* A [[Wilderness crabs teleport]] is the fastest way to reach Venenatis, and will teleport you to the dark crab fishing spot just south-east of the lair.
* With 90 [[Magic]], players on the [[Ancient spellbook]] can use [[Annakarl Teleport]], which will teleport them into the [[Demonic Ruins]]. Simply go south-east of your location after arriving. Be wary of [[PK'ers]] upon arrival.
** Alternatives to this also include the [[Annakarl teleport (tablet)|Annakarl teleport]] tablet and a portal attuned to Annakarl. Be wary of PK'ers on arrival; if using the house portal, you should have a [[scrying pool]] to check the area first.
* With 57 [[Woodcutting]], players can make a [[Waka canoe]] and use it to go to the [[Wilderness]]. Go east of your location past Vet'ion's rest and the poisonous spiders.
* A [[games necklace]] to teleport to the [[Corporeal Beast]]'s lair, exit the cave then run north-east.
* Players who have completed the Hard [[Wilderness Diary]] can utilize the Wilderness obelisks to teleport to levels 19, 35, or 55 to get closer to the Silk Chasm.
* Players who have completed the Hard or Elite [[Wilderness Diary]] can use the [[Wilderness Sword 4|Wilderness Sword]] to teleport to the [[Fountain of Rune]] and run south-west to Venenatis.

==Attacks==
Venenatis has many attacks that she uses against her target. 

*[[Melee]] attack: She simply lunges at the player
*Ranged attack: Launches green spit at players
*Magic attack: Launches webs at players
*Sticky Web: Venenatis will occasionally deploy a sticky web at a player, sending a white-blue web at the target's location. It will then expand into a 7x5 AoE - while in this web, any player caught in it will take rapid hits of 3 damage, have their prayer drained by 3, and run energy by 10.
**Note that [[aranea boots]] will only negate the first tick of damage taken from the web attack. Because of this, it is not recommended to use them at Venenatis due to the extremely small benefit they will provide, while adding unnecessary risk.
*Spiderlings: Venenatis will occasionally call some [[Venenatis' Spiderling (monster)|spiderlings]] to assist her in battle. While fairly weak, they will drain prayer on every hit regardless if prayed against or hits. They will also increase her damage and allow her to hit through prayers if left alive.  Thrall damage is reduced while spiderlings are alive.

