==Example ranged setup==

The [[Masori body (f)]] can be traded out for a [[Black d'hide body]] and [[Dinh's bulwark]] for survivability and AoE damage against the spiderlings. Ranged allows the player to more easily damage the enemy for the duration of the entire fight, and stand closer to the door where it may be more safe. In lower risk gear, the damage output of the bow doesn't match up to melee; the difference is [https://dps.osrs.wiki?id=KebbitRobberyTrap significant]. 

Additionally, due to the bows faster attack speed, the player consumes more revenant ether than if they were using melee. This is compounded by the longer fights with more hits. Because of this, extra ether is risked and used for slower fights, reducing potential profits.

As with melee, the player can use [[bracelet of slaughter]] to extend the task, if on a boss task for Venenatis. This will affect the player's accuracy and magic defence slightly.

